Two shaded quarter-circles, each with a radius of 4 units, are formed in the 4 by 8 rectangular region shown. What is the area of the non-shaded region, in square units? Express the area in the form $a - b\pi$ where $a$ and $b$ are integers.

\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.5]
% Draw the rectangle
\draw (0,0) rectangle (8,4);
% Fill the rectangle with gray
\fill[gray] (0,0) rectangle (8,4);
% Draw white quarter circles (non-shaded regions)
\fill[white] (4,0) arc (0:90:4) -- (0,0) -- cycle;
\fill[white] (4,0) arc (180:90:4) -- (8,0) -- cycle;
% Draw the arcs
\draw (4,0) arc (0:90:4);
\draw (4,0) arc (180:90:4);
% Draw the rectangle outline
\draw (0,0) rectangle (8,4);
% Labels
\node at (4,-0.5) {8};
\node at (8.5,2) {4};
\end{tikzpicture}
